@startuml AC-08_Telemetry_DoS

title AC-08 — Coordinated Compromised VM Fleet Floods Telemetry Database\nSTRIDE: Denial of Service | Severity: High | Mitigation: M-08

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Vending Machine\n(Legitimate)" as machine #DDEEFF
actor "Compromised VM Fleet\n(Stolen mTLS Certs)" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Report Machine Telemetry\nat Normal Rate (~1 req/min)" as UC8 << normal >>
  usecase "Extract mTLS Certs\nfrom Compromised Machines" as AC8a << abuse >>
  usecase "Flood Telemetry Endpoint\n(200 req/s per machine)" as AC8 << abuse >>
  usecase "Exhaust MySQL Disk /\nSaturate Thread Pool" as AC8b << abuse >>
}

machine --> UC8

attacker --> AC8a
AC8a ..> AC8   : <<enables>>
AC8 ..> UC8    : <<threatens>>
AC8 ..> AC8b   : <<extends>>

note right of AC8a
  **Preconditions:**
  • mTLS certs extracted from N >= 10
    physically/logically compromised VMs
  • No per-machine request-rate limit on EP2
    beyond mTLS authentication check
  • Telemetry table has no DB-level retention
    or write-throttle policy
  • Telemetry DB shares same MySQL instance
    disk as users/sales/inventory tables
end note

note right of AC8b
  **Impact:**
  Availability: disk fills ~33 GB/hour at
  N=10 machines × 200 req/s × 200 bytes/row
  Integrity: in-flight Sale transactions fail
  mid-commit → partial/corrupt records
  Business: purchase failures, SLA breach,
  inability to produce compliance audit logs
  Recovery: disk cleanup + telemetry truncation
  (data loss required)
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vector:**
  N machines × 200 req/s = 2,000+ concurrent inserts
  vs. legitimate rate: ~1 req/min per machine
  All requests carry valid mTLS certs —
  backend authenticates each as legitimate
end note

@enduml
